<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-24T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9637: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-24T19:00:00+09:00">August 24, 1937—7
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 24—7:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>307. Embassy’s 297, August 23, 1 p.m. In conversation today with the
                                Naval Attaché, the Senior Aide to the Navy Minister stated that full
                                evacuation of all Japanese from Tsingtao is in process and will be
                                completed within a few days. He added that landing of Japanese
                                forces will be avoided if at all possible.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>